05/02/2004
RIJEKA, Croatia -- European Integration Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic said Wednesday (4 February) the country's ambition to join the EU in 2007 is realistic. Speaking to students at the Rijeka School of Law, she expressed confidence the country will be allowed to start EU accession negotiations this year.
In Budapest meanwhile, parliament speakers from EU countries backed Croatia's application for accession negotiations, and offered support to efforts by Bulgaria and Romania to wrap up accession negotiations by the end of the year. (Jutarnji List, Vjesnik - 05/02/04; HINA, HRT - 04/02/04)
